{"parentUuid":"e096295f-f70a-4ab2-9e26-62c687b64739","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/nick/work/libnn","sessionId":"e0f1ea34-1b45-4ca5-accb-9980f0c7e0ac","version":"2.1.72","gitBranch":"develop","agentId":"aside_question-d81993e73b719612","slug":"snazzy-tumbling-penguin","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014ojcFsGV2vjyq2XmFCs2Dc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: Build and Test Environment for libnn\n     3→description: Andes toolchain, QEMU paths, FPGA board connection, and commands for building/testing libnn on AX45MPV with RVV\n     4→type: reference\n     5→---\n     6→\n     7→## Andes Toolchain (ast530 — primary)\n     8→- Path: `/local/nick/SW_Release_cp/ast530/nds64le-elf-newlib-v5d/bin/`\n     9→- Compiler: `riscv64-elf-gcc` (Andes v5d, GCC 12.2.0)\n    10→- Must be first on PATH to override system riscv64-elf-gcc (which lacks Andes extensions like `-mext-vector`)\n    11→- libnn headers are pre-installed in this toolchain's sysroot (`riscv64-elf/include/`)\n    12→- Note: ast540 (GCC 14.2.0, at `/local/nick/build-ast540/bin/`) exists but does NOT have libnn headers installed in its sysroot — do not use for BS3 test.sh runs without installing headers first\n    13→\n    14→## FPGA Board (for cycle-accurate performance measurement)\n    15→- Board host: `sw-boards.andestech.com`\n    16→- Port: `1116`\n    17→- Env vars needed: `export MYPC=sw-boards.andestech.com` and `export MYPORT=1116`\n    18→- Wrapper: `riscv64-sim-wrapper-on-board` (uses GDB expect script `gdb-ice-riscv64.exp`)\n    19→- Test command:\n    20→```bash\n    21→cd /home/nick/work/libnn/build_perf_ax45mpv\n    22→export PATH=\"/local/nick/SW_Release_cp/ast530/nds64le-elf-newlib-v5d/bin:/home/nick/work/libnn:$PATH\"\n    23→export MYPC=sw-boards.andestech.com\n    24→export MYPORT=1116\n    25→rm -f /home/nick/work/libnn/project/ax45mpv/First_Reset_done\n    26→../test.sh \"\" riscv64-elf-gcc /home/nick/work/libnn/project/ax45mpv/riscv64-sim-wrapper-on-board BOARD BS3 \"-mtune=andes-45-series -mext-vector -DNDS_VEC_RVV_VERSION=1000 -DENA_RUN_TWICE -DENA_CACHEABLE_ENV_SETUP -lnn_v -mzfh -DENA_TEST_PERF -DENA_DUMP_PARAMETERS\"\n    27→```\n    28→\n    29→## QEMU (Andes fork — for functional testing)\n    30→- Binary: `/local/nick/qemu_andes/build/qemu-system-riscv64` (QEMU 9.2.0, Andes fork)\n    31→- Env var: `export QEMU_SYS_RV64=/local/nick/qemu_andes/build/qemu-system-riscv64`\n    32→- Supports all Andes CPU models (ax45mpv, nx27v, ax66, etc.) and `andes_ae350` machine\n    33→\n    34→## Running Unit Tests for AX45MPV (QEMU mode)\n    35→\n    36→```bash\n    37→cd /home/nick/work/libnn/project/ax45mpv\n    38→export QEMU_SYS_RV64=/local/nick/qemu_andes/build/qemu-system-riscv64\n    39→export PATH=\"/local/nick/SW_Release_cp/ast530/nds64le-elf-newlib-v5d/bin:/home/nick/work/libnn:$PATH\"\n    40→bash ./run.sh\n    41→```\n    42→\n    43→- `run.sh` has `RUN_CONFIG=2` (QEMU mode) by default\n    44→- Default wrapper: `riscv-qemu-wrapper-v512_d512_b512` (VLEN=512)\n    45→- For VLEN=1024: change to `riscv-qemu-wrapper-v1024_d1024_b512` in run.sh line ~101\n    46→- CPU model used: `andes-ax45mpv,vext_spec=v1.0,vlen={512|1024}`\n    47→\n    48→## User's Focus\n    49→- Primary target: AX45MPV with VLEN=1024 (`v1024_d1024_b512`)\n    50→- 294/294 unit tests pass at 100% (verified 2026-03-20)\n    51→\n    52→## Running a Single Test via QEMU\n    53→\n    54→```bash\n    55→export QEMU_SYS_RV64=/local/nick/qemu_andes/build/qemu-system-riscv64\n    56→/home/nick/work/libnn/project/ax45mpv/riscv-qemu-wrapper-v1024_d1024_b512 path/to/test.adx\n    57→```\n    58→"}]},"uuid":"d8671e66-79d4-4cde-ac77-218915c95090","timestamp":"2026-03-21T08:15:06.208Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/nick/.claude/projects/-home-nick-work-libnn/memory/reference_build_test_env.md","content":"---\nname: Build and Test Environment for libnn\ndescription: Andes toolchain, QEMU paths, FPGA board connection, and commands for building/testing libnn on AX45MPV with RVV\ntype: reference\n---\n\n## Andes Toolchain (ast530 — primary)\n- Path: `/local/nick/SW_Release_cp/ast530/nds64le-elf-newlib-v5d/bin/`\n- Compiler: `riscv64-elf-gcc` (Andes v5d, GCC 12.2.0)\n- Must be first on PATH to override system riscv64-elf-gcc (which lacks Andes extensions like `-mext-vector`)\n- libnn headers are pre-installed in this toolchain's sysroot (`riscv64-elf/include/`)\n- Note: ast540 (GCC 14.2.0, at `/local/nick/build-ast540/bin/`) exists but does NOT have libnn headers installed in its sysroot — do not use for BS3 test.sh runs without installing headers first\n\n## FPGA Board (for cycle-accurate performance measurement)\n- Board host: `sw-boards.andestech.com`\n- Port: `1116`\n- Env vars needed: `export MYPC=sw-boards.andestech.com` and `export MYPORT=1116`\n- Wrapper: `riscv64-sim-wrapper-on-board` (uses GDB expect script `gdb-ice-riscv64.exp`)\n- Test command:\n```bash\ncd /home/nick/work/libnn/build_perf_ax45mpv\nexport PATH=\"/local/nick/SW_Release_cp/ast530/nds64le-elf-newlib-v5d/bin:/home/nick/work/libnn:$PATH\"\nexport MYPC=sw-boards.andestech.com\nexport MYPORT=1116\nrm -f /home/nick/work/libnn/project/ax45mpv/First_Reset_done\n../test.sh \"\" riscv64-elf-gcc /home/nick/work/libnn/project/ax45mpv/riscv64-sim-wrapper-on-board BOARD BS3 \"-mtune=andes-45-series -mext-vector -DNDS_VEC_RVV_VERSION=1000 -DENA_RUN_TWICE -DENA_CACHEABLE_ENV_SETUP -lnn_v -mzfh -DENA_TEST_PERF -DENA_DUMP_PARAMETERS\"\n```\n\n## QEMU (Andes fork — for functional testing)\n- Binary: `/local/nick/qemu_andes/build/qemu-system-riscv64` (QEMU 9.2.0, Andes fork)\n- Env var: `export QEMU_SYS_RV64=/local/nick/qemu_andes/build/qemu-system-riscv64`\n- Supports all Andes CPU models (ax45mpv, nx27v, ax66, etc.) and `andes_ae350` machine\n\n## Running Unit Tests for AX45MPV (QEMU mode)\n\n```bash\ncd /home/nick/work/libnn/project/ax45mpv\nexport QEMU_SYS_RV64=/local/nick/qemu_andes/build/qemu-system-riscv64\nexport PATH=\"/local/nick/SW_Release_cp/ast530/nds64le-elf-newlib-v5d/bin:/home/nick/work/libnn:$PATH\"\nbash ./run.sh\n```\n\n- `run.sh` has `RUN_CONFIG=2` (QEMU mode) by default\n- Default wrapper: `riscv-qemu-wrapper-v512_d512_b512` (VLEN=512)\n- For VLEN=1024: change to `riscv-qemu-wrapper-v1024_d1024_b512` in run.sh line ~101\n- CPU model used: `andes-ax45mpv,vext_spec=v1.0,vlen={512|1024}`\n\n## User's Focus\n- Primary target: AX45MPV with VLEN=1024 (`v1024_d1024_b512`)\n- 294/294 unit tests pass at 100% (verified 2026-03-20)\n\n## Running a Single Test via QEMU\n\n```bash\nexport QEMU_SYS_RV64=/local/nick/qemu_andes/build/qemu-system-riscv64\n/home/nick/work/libnn/project/ax45mpv/riscv-qemu-wrapper-v1024_d1024_b512 path/to/test.adx\n```\n","numLines":58,"startLine":1,"totalLines":58}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"e096295f-f70a-4ab2-9e26-62c687b64739"}
